    "recap_headline": "University of North Carolina Ashville Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CLINTON, S.C. -\nUNC Asheville Baseball dropped the rubber game of its opening Big South Conference series at Presbyterian on Sunday (Mar. 15) by a score of 11-1 in seven innings.\nThe Bulldogs scored the first run of the game in the top of the first when\nLogan Lowe\nscored on a RBI single to left by\nJake Minarik\n, before Presbyterian responded with two runs in the second, two in the third, four in the fourth and three in the sixth to bring the game to its final score.\nLogan Lowe\n, Minarik,\nOwen Michelson\n,\nEric Krumpe\nand\nColeman McGinnis\neach had one hit in the game for Asheville. Krumpe had Asheville's lone extra-base hit in the game with a double. Lowe scored Asheville's lone run in the game, while Minarik drove in the run for the Bulldogs. Lowe also stole one base in the game.\nDrew Turner\n(3-2) took the loss on the bump for Asheville, allowing two runs on two hits with two walks and four strikeouts in the game.\nGarrett Crum\ntook the next inning, before\nBranden Barna\nand\nLucas Boesen\nfinished off the game for the Bulldog pitching staff. McGinnis also gunned down one runner in the game.\nThe Bulldogs (11-10, 1-2 Big South Conference) return to action on Tuesday (Mar. 17) hosting East Tennessee State in non-conference action. First pitch is set for 4:00 p.m. from Greenwood Field with\nvideo\nand\nlive stats\navailable at\nwww.uncabulldogs.com\n.\nA reminder that admission to all UNC Asheville Baseball games at Greenwood Field is free courtesy of\nIngles\n!"
  },
